[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '600 languages, zero-shot voice cloning, and the whole thing runs under 8 GB of VRAM. That\'s OmniVoice, and honestly, it might be the most impressive lightweight TTS model I\'ve tested all year. Here\'s why this actually matters. Most'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'text-to-speech models are either massive, locked behind a paywall, or fall apart the moment you throw anything other than English at them. Eleven Labs is great, sure, but it costs money, and its multilingual support is nowhere near'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this level. OmniVoice supports 600 languages, including languages so obscure you\'d struggle to find any AI model that even recognizes them. And I\'ve put together a free Google Colab'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'notebook so you can run this yourself, unlimited, no GPU required on your end. I spent a good chunk of time building that notebook, so make sure you grab it. Before we get into the setup, though, let me show you what this thing actually'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'does on their official demo page. They\'ve got hundreds of audio samples across 102 languages. English, Thai, Korean, Persian, Bengali, Greek, Dutch, all in a drop-down. You pick a language'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
