AUDIO: 'This is where the multilingual depth of this model starts to hit differently. These aren\'t major global languages with'

[02:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'massive training data sets behind them. These are secondary, regional, sometimes obscure languages, and OmniVoice is handling them with a level of confidence that\'s genuinely rare. Here\'s where it gets really interesting. Cross-lingual'

[02:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'zero-shot TTS. What this means is you give it a voice sample in one language, and you ask it to speak text in a completely different language. Entirely different phonetics, different mouth'

[03:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shapes, different rhythm. Let me show you. This is a Chinese input audio. Now listen to the output in English.'

[03:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Suddenly, there was a burst of laughter beside me. I looked at them, stood up straight with high spirit. The vocal character carries across, the timbre, the resonance, the'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'subtle texture of the voice, it transfers across a language boundary. Now, let\'s flip it. English input. Some call me nature. Others call me Mother Nature.'

[03:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; And now, the same voice speaking Chinese. That is cross-lingual voice cloning working at a level I honestly didn\'t'

[03:55] [scene:talk]
